  "texts": [
    "While there are no strict guidelines for determining the ideal number of participants for qualitative research, researchers commonly suggest that a participant range of 10-50 individuals is often considered adequate.",
    "This adequacy depends on the nature of the research and the specific inquiries pursued (Creswell & Creswell, 2018).",
    "The prospective participants received emails outlining the study's objectives, the confidential nature of their responses, the expected time commitment for the interview, and the voluntary nature of their involvement.",
    "Additionally, the participants were informed that the interviews would be recorded for transcription purposes.",
    "Prior to commencing each interview, a comprehensive introduction was provided to elucidate the purpose of the study and ensure the confidentiality of their responses."
  ],
